{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, incorporating diversity ensures that the search is directed towards a comprehensive exploration of the entire possible input space.",
    "This method effectively captures the extent to which each individual contributes to the genetic diversity of the population.",
    "By quantifying diversity in this manner, the fitness function enables a nuanced assessment of each individual's uniqueness, fostering a selection process that emphasizes the maintenance and enhancement of population diversity.",
    "This approach is particularly valuable in evolutionary algorithms, where diversity is crucial for avoiding premature convergence to sub-optimal solutions and for ensuring a comprehensive exploration of the search space.Based on the above discussion, we would have multi-objective fitness function including execution time and diversity.",
    "The diversity fitness function is calculated using QMC Discrepancy, which was discussed in Section 2.1, of current points in the solution space."
  ]
}